\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 # AI Review Protocol\cb1 \
\cb3 **Project:** KitchenGuard  \cb1 \
\cb3 **Purpose:** Safer AI-assisted development with better review, fewer regressions, and clearer merge decisions.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## Core Principle\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Use **different agents for different jobs**.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Do **not** use multiple agents all making uncontrolled edits to the same branch.  \cb1 \
\cb3 Instead, use a simple pipeline:\cb1 \
\
\cb3 1. **Plan** the change\cb1 \
\cb3 2. **Implement** the change\cb1 \
\cb3 3. **Review** the diff\cb1 \
\cb3 4. **Test** the behavior\cb1 \
\cb3 5. **Approve** manually before merge\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ## Default Workflow\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ### For small changes\cb1 \
\cb3 Use this when:\cb1 \
\cb3 - UI polish\cb1 \
\cb3 - text changes\cb1 \
\cb3 - small bug fixes\cb1 \
\cb3 - isolated screen behavior changes\cb1 \
\
\cb3 **Flow**\cb1 \
\cb3 1. Builder agent implements the change\cb1 \
\cb3 2. Reviewer agent reviews the diff only\cb1 \
\cb3 3. Test agent adds or suggests a regression test\cb1 \
\cb3 4. Run app + lint/tests\cb1 \
\cb3 5. Human reviews and merges\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ### For medium changes\cb1 \
\cb3 Use this when:\cb1 \
\cb3 - state handling changes\cb1 \
